answers.body_markdown:
`NoSuchFileException` indicates that the directory you&#39;re trying to list or delete in `FileUploadUtil.cleanDir` doesn&#39;t exist, so you may want to first - check it&#39;s there, and if not - mkdir() it, like:

```java
String uploadDir = &quot;../category-images/&quot; + savedCategory.getId();
File directory = new File(uploadDir);
if (!directory.exists()) {
    directory.mkdirs();
}
FileUploadUtil.cleanDir(uploadDir);
FileUploadUtil.saveFile(uploadDir, fileName, multipartFile);
```
My gut feeling also tells me that you&#39;re trying to save files to a directory relative to your application&#39;s current directory with the path `../category-images/`, but it&#39;s better to follow the common practice, of keeping static resources like images within the application&#39;s classpath, typically inside `src/main/resources`. When you build your application into a JAR or WAR file, these resources are nicely bundled up and easily accessible, so maybe the real cause of your problem is right there.

